The Osun Government has condemned the killing of the Chairman of All Progressives Congress (APC), Chief Gbenga Ogbara in Atakumosa-East Central local government of the State. A statement issued by the Chief Press Secretary to Governor Gboyega Oyetola, Ismail Omipidan, said a delegation has visited the family of the late Abiola Afolabi who was allegedly killed by the police. The state government charged security operatives to fish out the perpetrators and ensure justice is served while it sympathized with the family of the assassinated chairman and Afolabi’s family. The government delegation to the family of the late Abiola Afolabi was led by the Special Adviser to the governor on Security, Mrs. Abiodun Ige. Ige, during the visit, assured the family of the government’s interest in unravelling the circumstances leading to the alleged killing of the late Abiola and ensured that he did not die in vain. The Government further noted that the probe would help to prevent future occurrences and ensure that those responsible are decisively dealt with. “As a government, we are resolved to do everything possible to protect citizens from actual and potential threats. To this end, we have ordered security beef up around the Igangan area. “We have also directed security operatives to launch an extensive manhunt so as to fish out those responsible for the killing of the late APC chieftain. “Government enjoins all citizens to be peaceful and to be law-abiding as all efforts shall be made to protect them and their property at all times, ” the Government added.